267
00:20:08,585 --> 00:20:10,145
This time, no matter what,

268
00:20:10,665 --> 00:20:12,665
we'll find out exactly how he died.

269
00:20:13,185 --> 00:20:14,105
Otherwise,

270
00:20:15,145 --> 00:20:17,065
I don't deserve this badge.

271
00:20:20,545 --> 00:20:21,625
Qu,

272
00:20:22,945 --> 00:20:24,105
a New Year's gift.

273
00:20:24,705 --> 00:20:26,425
Steep it and drink it. It helps grow hair.

274
00:20:27,425 --> 00:20:30,305
Captain, that's so thoughtful. I…

275
00:20:32,465 --> 00:20:33,545
Happy New Year.

276
00:20:34,065 --> 00:20:35,465
You too. I'll get going.

277
00:20:50,745 --> 00:20:52,985
JIANGDONG WEST ROAD

278
00:21:15,345 --> 00:21:17,465
RAN FANGXU'S PATH

279
00:21:24,265 --> 00:21:25,105
Ran…

280
00:21:25,785 --> 00:21:28,265
Where did you put the evidence?

281
00:21:28,945 --> 00:21:31,305
Why do I have no clue now?

282
00:21:41,705 --> 00:21:42,545
Hey.

283
00:21:42,625 --> 00:21:45,385
Mr. He, are you okay?

284
00:21:46,185 --> 00:21:47,345
<i>I'm fine.</i>

285
00:21:47,425 --> 00:21:49,505
Go handle your work.

286
00:21:49,585 --> 00:21:50,945
Don't worry.

287
00:21:51,465 --> 00:21:53,945
Qu and Xiaohe
are checking traffic footage.

288
00:21:54,665 --> 00:21:56,545
<i>I'm reviewing Qiao Suqing's interrogation.</i>

289
00:21:56,625 --> 00:21:58,705
Seeing if she slipped up anywhere.

290
00:21:59,465 --> 00:22:00,305
<i>By the way,</i>

291
00:22:00,385 --> 00:22:02,825
Ran's belongings… Who sorted them?

292
00:22:02,905 --> 00:22:04,665
<i>Could something be missing?</i>

293
00:22:06,305 --> 00:22:08,465
I handled his home myself, personally.

294
00:22:08,545 --> 00:22:09,505
Nothing should be missing.

295
00:22:09,585 --> 00:22:12,265
<i>As for police items,</i>
<i>Wang Mangkun sorted them.</i>

296
00:22:12,345 --> 00:22:13,505
Need me to ask him?

297
00:22:13,585 --> 00:22:14,745
I can have him call you.

298
00:22:14,825 --> 00:22:17,465
No need. I'll contact him myself.

299
00:22:17,545 --> 00:22:19,225
<i>That's it for now.</i>

300
00:22:21,025 --> 00:22:21,905
Mr. He…

301
00:22:21,985 --> 00:22:22,825
<i>Go on.</i>

302
00:22:24,745 --> 00:22:26,025
You've been through a lot

303
00:22:28,545 --> 00:22:29,465
these past two years.

304
00:22:30,505 --> 00:22:33,545
<i>You've stuck with this case</i>

305
00:22:34,545 --> 00:22:35,705
and his last wish.

306
00:22:37,905 --> 00:22:38,945
About this…

307
00:22:41,945 --> 00:22:42,945
I feel guilty.

308
00:22:45,705 --> 00:22:46,545
I…

309
00:22:48,625 --> 00:22:49,865
was too late to realize.

310
00:22:53,105 --> 00:22:54,985
<i>I failed as a detective.</i>

311
00:22:59,345 --> 00:23:00,505
But don't worry.

312
00:23:02,385 --> 00:23:04,185
From now on, I'll give it everything.

313
00:23:04,905 --> 00:23:07,705
<i>I'll do whatever it takes</i>
<i>to find the truth.</i>

314
00:23:08,345 --> 00:23:11,265
<i>I won't let the one who killed him go.</i>

315
00:23:12,785 --> 00:23:14,145
Nor will I let him

316
00:23:15,985 --> 00:23:17,225
die without answers.

317
00:23:23,585 --> 00:23:24,665
You kid,

318
00:23:25,785 --> 00:23:28,025
it's not too late to think like this.

319
00:23:28,945 --> 00:23:30,425
<i>Get back to work.</i>

320
00:23:31,465 --> 00:23:32,345
<i>I'm hanging up.</i>

321
00:23:50,385 --> 00:23:51,345
JIANGDONG WEST ROAD

322
00:23:52,665 --> 00:23:53,665
JIANGDONG NORTH ROAD

323
00:23:55,625 --> 00:23:57,505
‎JAN 31, 2003. 2:35:20 PM
‎JIANGXI EAST ROAD

324
00:24:06,345 --> 00:24:07,425
‎JAN 31, 2003. 4:24:16 PM
‎JIANGDONG SOUTH ROAD

325
00:24:10,505 --> 00:24:11,865
‎JAN 31, 2003. 8:00:06 PM
‎JIANGXI MID ROAD

326
00:24:13,745 --> 00:24:14,865
‎JAN 31, 2003. 7:30:51 PM
‎JIANGDONG NORTH ROAD

327
00:24:19,985 --> 00:24:21,625
‎JAN 31, 2003. 7:26:31 PM
‎JIANGDONG MID ROAD

328
00:24:27,145 --> 00:24:28,145
Xiaohe,

329
00:24:29,665 --> 00:24:30,785
take a look.

330
00:24:31,785 --> 00:24:34,425
Can you tell if it's Qiao Suqing?

331
00:24:47,505 --> 00:24:48,545
Don't rush.

332
00:24:48,625 --> 00:24:49,945
Let's keep checking outward.

333
00:24:50,585 --> 00:24:52,345
If not at night, then check daytime.

334
00:24:52,945 --> 00:24:54,545
We'll find her.

335
00:25:17,945 --> 00:25:20,265
MAJOR LANDSLIDE HIT MOUNT WU
IN KUNHAI YESTERDAY

336
00:25:33,265 --> 00:25:35,465
Sir, be careful.

337
00:25:35,545 --> 00:25:37,265
Did you forget about your blood pressure?

338
00:25:38,225 --> 00:25:40,665
Ran, what took you so long?

339
00:25:40,745 --> 00:25:42,185
I've got so much to ask.

340
00:25:42,785 --> 00:25:44,785
Back then, when you found Qiao Suqing,

341
00:25:45,345 --> 00:25:48,745
you must've had solid evidence, right?

342
00:25:53,705 --> 00:25:55,545
Then where did you put it…

343
00:26:09,865 --> 00:26:12,105
Sir, what did you say?

344
00:26:12,185 --> 00:26:13,345
I can't hear you.

345
00:26:14,865 --> 00:26:15,985
I said,

346
00:26:16,065 --> 00:26:20,745
the evidence you used
to identify Qiao Suqing, where is it?

347
00:26:27,865 --> 00:26:28,705
What did you say?

348
00:26:30,425 --> 00:26:31,505
Hold on!

349
00:26:37,225 --> 00:26:38,305
Go ahead!

350
00:26:40,905 --> 00:26:41,945
Oh.

351
00:26:51,185 --> 00:26:53,105
You… Don't worry about me!

352
00:26:53,865 --> 00:26:55,945
I'm doing fine!

353
00:26:56,025 --> 00:26:58,185
Xiaohe's fine too!

354
00:26:58,265 --> 00:26:59,625
Zhao Jie's fine!

355
00:26:59,705 --> 00:27:01,745
We're all doing well!

356
00:27:01,825 --> 00:27:03,185
So don't worry!

357
00:27:16,225 --> 00:27:17,265
Ran…

358
00:27:23,585 --> 00:27:24,665
Ran…

359
00:27:25,585 --> 00:27:26,865
Ran…

360
00:27:29,745 --> 00:27:30,945
Ran…

361
00:28:09,745 --> 00:28:12,745
ICU FAMILY VISITING ROOM

362
00:28:13,825 --> 00:28:15,785
Doctor, how's my dad?

363
00:28:15,865 --> 00:28:16,705
Which one is your dad?

364
00:28:17,345 --> 00:28:18,705
This one.

365
00:28:18,785 --> 00:28:20,665
Don't worry. He's not in danger.

366
00:28:20,745 --> 00:28:23,545
But he has weak vessels,
overworked lately,

367
00:28:23,625 --> 00:28:25,385
and missed his meds,

368
00:28:25,465 --> 00:28:28,025
triggering an ischemic stroke.

369
00:28:28,105 --> 00:28:30,185
He needs to stay for observation.

370
00:28:30,265 --> 00:28:31,345
Thank you, Doctor.

371
00:28:31,425 --> 00:28:32,265
You're welcome.

372
00:28:34,065 --> 00:28:34,945
Manager Ma, thank you.

373
00:28:35,025 --> 00:28:36,305
It's nothing, really.

374
00:28:36,385 --> 00:28:38,225
It's our job.

375
00:28:38,305 --> 00:28:39,425
As long as Yuanlongli stands,

376
00:28:39,505 --> 00:28:42,545
I'll do my duty as property manager.

377
00:28:43,065 --> 00:28:43,985
By the way,

378
00:28:44,745 --> 00:28:47,425
this was in Mr. He's hand
when he collapsed.

379
00:28:47,505 --> 00:28:49,865
It took effort to pry it out.

380
00:28:50,425 --> 00:28:51,945
I'll head back first.

381
00:28:52,025 --> 00:28:53,625
If you need anything, just call me.

382
00:28:54,225 --> 00:28:55,905
-Thanks.
-No problem.

383
00:29:08,505 --> 00:29:09,585
What happened?

384
00:29:09,665 --> 00:29:10,625
I was on the phone with him,

385
00:29:10,705 --> 00:29:11,625
and he suddenly fainted?

386
00:29:11,705 --> 00:29:12,905
Doctor said it's nothing serious.

387
00:29:12,985 --> 00:29:14,785
Just overwork triggering his condition.

388
00:29:16,545 --> 00:29:17,985
That's a relief.

389
00:29:18,665 --> 00:29:19,705
How about this?

390
00:29:19,785 --> 00:29:21,505
Work can wait. Put it aside.

391
00:29:21,585 --> 00:29:22,945
Stay and take care of him.

392
00:29:23,025 --> 00:29:23,905
Captain…

393
00:29:24,545 --> 00:29:27,705
My dad's in there, and I can't help much.

394
00:29:27,785 --> 00:29:30,905
I'd rather work the case
and find the truth.

395
00:29:34,505 --> 00:29:36,305
The June 30 case is reopened.

396
00:29:36,385 --> 00:29:38,145
Xiaohe should lead it.

397
00:29:38,225 --> 00:29:40,865
The team and I will back her up.

398
00:29:41,865 --> 00:29:43,265
And besides, solving it

399
00:29:43,865 --> 00:29:45,345
isn't just Ran's wish,

400
00:29:45,865 --> 00:29:47,385
it's He Yuanhang's too.

401
00:29:55,625 --> 00:29:56,465
Alright.

402
00:29:56,985 --> 00:29:58,305
Talk to the doctor,

403
00:29:58,385 --> 00:30:00,145
-then get back ASAP.
-Thank you, Captain.

404
00:30:06,145 --> 00:30:08,065
Before I came, I found another clip.

405
00:30:08,145 --> 00:30:10,825
Same woman with the umbrella.
I copied it for you.

406
00:30:11,425 --> 00:30:13,065
Two drives left to check.

407
00:30:13,145 --> 00:30:14,265
I'll head back and continue.

408
00:30:14,865 --> 00:30:15,705
Captain Qu!

409
00:30:18,025 --> 00:30:19,225
Thank you.

410
00:30:21,105 --> 00:30:22,345
What's with you?

411
00:30:22,425 --> 00:30:23,745
Thanking me twice today.

412
00:30:24,785 --> 00:30:27,945
Last time, it was for my uncle.

413
00:30:29,065 --> 00:30:31,905
This time, it's for my dad.

414
00:30:40,465 --> 00:30:42,705
The two of us worked together for years.

415
00:30:44,505 --> 00:30:45,905
Seeing him now,

416
00:30:46,425 --> 00:30:48,785
lying there against his will…

417
00:30:50,545 --> 00:30:51,865
It just

418
00:30:53,225 --> 00:30:54,665
doesn't feel good.

419
00:31:03,345 --> 00:31:05,465
When he's better, tell him

420
00:31:06,065 --> 00:31:07,505
he owes me one.

421
00:31:08,625 --> 00:31:09,665
I'm off.

422
00:31:11,465 --> 00:31:12,905
Captain Qu!

423
00:31:41,345 --> 00:31:44,465
FAIR AND JUST

424
00:31:44,545 --> 00:31:45,785
<i>This whole explanation,</i>

425
00:31:46,305 --> 00:31:49,025
<i>you must've planned for years, didn't you?</i>

426
00:31:50,145 --> 00:31:51,185
<i>Xiaohe.</i>

427
00:31:55,105 --> 00:31:55,985
JULY 1, WEDNESDAY

428
00:31:56,065 --> 00:31:59,105
<i>I even admitted I pushed my own mother</i>
<i>off a cliff by accident.</i>

429
00:31:59,185 --> 00:32:00,705
<i>I told you that myself.</i>

430
00:32:01,225 --> 00:32:03,345
<i>So making up anything else,</i>
<i>what would be the point?</i>

431
00:32:14,145 --> 00:32:15,665
CAPTAIN'S OFFICE

432
00:32:18,345 --> 00:32:19,945
Captain, reporting in.

433
00:32:20,025 --> 00:32:22,065
Qiao Suqing is assisting now.

434
00:32:22,145 --> 00:32:23,425
If we can't detain her,

435
00:32:23,505 --> 00:32:25,985
in three hours, the hold expires.

436
00:32:26,065 --> 00:32:27,785
Then we'll have to release her?

437
00:32:27,865 --> 00:32:29,545
Why so eager?

438
00:32:29,625 --> 00:32:30,585
We've got three hours.

439
00:32:30,665 --> 00:32:32,305
Get out! Don't bother me!

440
00:32:33,065 --> 00:32:33,945
Okay.

441
00:32:44,705 --> 00:32:47,705
COMPREHENSIVE SOCIAL SECURITY MANAGEMENT

442
00:32:55,745 --> 00:32:58,505
Qu said you made some progress
with the surveillance.

443
00:32:58,585 --> 00:32:59,865
Why are you just sitting here?

444
00:33:00,465 --> 00:33:02,385
The footage, it's just a lead.

445
00:33:02,905 --> 00:33:04,545
We still lack proof.

446
00:33:06,145 --> 00:33:08,265
This note my dad wrote
before he collapsed…

447
00:33:08,345 --> 00:33:10,065
I keep thinking,

448
00:33:10,145 --> 00:33:13,145
could it be linked to what
Uncle Ran found?

449
00:33:19,905 --> 00:33:22,785
Captain Zhao said before Mr. He collapsed,

450
00:33:23,305 --> 00:33:26,385
he asked about Ran's belongings.

451
00:33:26,465 --> 00:33:29,425
Back then, I handled that.

452
00:33:29,945 --> 00:33:31,985
I even went back and checked again.

453
00:33:32,065 --> 00:33:33,585
It was all routine files.

454
00:33:33,665 --> 00:33:39,025
Whether paper or digital,
nothing stood out.

455
00:33:43,825 --> 00:33:45,425
Digital…

456
00:33:47,465 --> 00:33:48,625
The office system?

457
00:33:48,705 --> 00:33:49,825
No way.

458
00:33:49,905 --> 00:33:53,545
I took over his account
and internal email.

459
00:33:54,225 --> 00:33:55,785
Nothing unusual.

460
00:33:55,865 --> 00:33:57,745
I remember that morning,

461
00:33:57,825 --> 00:33:59,425
he rushed back,

462
00:33:59,505 --> 00:34:01,865
didn't even greet anyone,
and went straight into his office.

463
00:34:01,945 --> 00:34:03,345
Wait… I remember.

464
00:34:03,425 --> 00:34:05,145
<i>I went in that day.</i>

465
00:34:05,665 --> 00:34:07,145
It's New Year… Why are you still busy?

466
00:34:07,945 --> 00:34:08,905
Nothing.

467
00:34:09,545 --> 00:34:11,784
Writing a case summary email.

468
00:34:11,865 --> 00:34:12,705
What case?

469
00:34:12,784 --> 00:34:13,865
I never heard of it.

470
00:34:16,025 --> 00:34:20,425
He was at his desk, said he was writing
a case summary email.

471
00:34:21,025 --> 00:34:23,665
That day, did any of you get his email?

472
00:34:28,465 --> 00:34:30,545
Could it be an internal email to my dad?

473
00:34:30,625 --> 00:34:31,784
No.

474
00:34:31,865 --> 00:34:33,865
Back then, he never used computers.

475
00:34:33,945 --> 00:34:36,905
His system account and internal email…

476
00:34:36,985 --> 00:34:37,985
He never used them.

477
00:34:39,264 --> 00:34:41,905
But the system account
is just full-name pinyin.

478
00:34:43,425 --> 00:34:46,985
Wait, you handle retired accounts, right?

479
00:34:47,065 --> 00:34:47,945
Captain,

480
00:34:48,865 --> 00:34:53,425
I actually came across Mr. He's account
while organizing the system.

481
00:34:53,505 --> 00:34:55,465
What are you waiting for? Log in, now.

482
00:34:55,545 --> 00:34:57,105
After I saw it,

483
00:34:58,225 --> 00:34:59,665
I deleted it.

484
00:35:00,425 --> 00:35:01,785
Why so eager?

485
00:35:10,985 --> 00:35:14,385
Liu, can you restore a deleted account?

486
00:35:14,465 --> 00:35:16,065
<i>A deleted account,</i>

487
00:35:16,145 --> 00:35:17,545
<i>if it needs recovery,</i>

488
00:35:17,625 --> 00:35:20,065
<i>we'd have to send the main drive</i>
<i>to the city IT center.</i>

489
00:35:20,145 --> 00:35:21,585
That won't work. How long would that take?

490
00:35:21,665 --> 00:35:22,865
I need it now.

491
00:35:22,945 --> 00:35:24,985
<i>Captain, that's beyond us.</i>

492
00:35:25,065 --> 00:35:27,665
<i>We're cops, not hackers.</i>

493
00:35:33,145 --> 00:35:34,065
Hackers?

494
00:35:36,065 --> 00:35:38,625
Check up and down, left and right…

495
00:35:39,145 --> 00:35:41,465
-He's a hacker.
-A hacker?

496
00:35:42,305 --> 00:35:43,665
I'm not a hacker.

497
00:35:43,745 --> 00:35:45,945
You got the wrong guy. I'm innocent.

498
00:35:46,025 --> 00:35:47,785
-Take him first!
-Move!

499
00:35:47,865 --> 00:35:49,385
-Wait…
-Come on.

500
00:35:49,465 --> 00:35:50,705
Where? My computer…

501
00:35:50,785 --> 00:35:52,065
Where are we going?

502
00:36:00,505 --> 00:36:03,625
POLICE USE ONLY

503
00:36:10,505 --> 00:36:11,825
Relax.

504
00:36:11,905 --> 00:36:13,265
We just need help on data recovery.

505
00:36:13,345 --> 00:36:14,745
It's approved.

506
00:36:14,825 --> 00:36:16,145
Handled technically.

507
00:36:16,225 --> 00:36:18,425
It's all legal and secure.

508
00:36:19,385 --> 00:36:20,385
Make way!

509
00:36:20,465 --> 00:36:22,105
Here's fuel for him.

510
00:36:22,185 --> 00:36:23,665
Here. Drink up.

511
00:36:41,105 --> 00:36:43,905
The system's hard drive… ever replaced?

512
00:36:43,985 --> 00:36:45,105
No.

513
00:36:46,065 --> 00:36:47,305
Five minutes.

514
00:37:21,785 --> 00:37:23,105
ENTER PASSWORD

515
00:37:26,265 --> 00:37:27,545
The data's still there.

516
00:37:28,625 --> 00:37:29,905
It's encrypted.

517
00:37:30,425 --> 00:37:31,705
If you don't know the password,

518
00:37:31,785 --> 00:37:33,825
I can install a hacking tool

519
00:37:33,905 --> 00:37:35,585
-and crack it.
-Are you crazy?

520
00:37:35,665 --> 00:37:38,025
Installing random software
on police computers?

521
00:37:38,105 --> 00:37:39,625
You want jail time?

522
00:37:45,305 --> 00:37:46,385
I'll try.

523
00:37:55,145 --> 00:37:56,625
ENTER PASSWORD

524
00:37:56,705 --> 00:37:57,545
ERROR

525
00:38:00,985 --> 00:38:02,345
I'll try a birthday.

526
00:38:02,425 --> 00:38:08,145
ENTER PASSWORD

527
00:38:08,225 --> 00:38:08,985
ERROR

528
00:38:14,265 --> 00:38:15,665
Wait!

529
00:38:15,745 --> 00:38:17,265
Last try.

530
00:38:17,345 --> 00:38:18,465
One more and it locks.

531
00:38:37,785 --> 00:38:39,585
Your teacher said

532
00:38:40,265 --> 00:38:41,865
you ranked

533
00:38:42,465 --> 00:38:43,585
last in finals.

534
00:38:46,785 --> 00:38:48,225
Last place is fine.

535
00:38:48,745 --> 00:38:49,865
Not so bad.

536
00:38:52,385 --> 00:38:53,905
Last place and still fine?

537
00:38:54,905 --> 00:38:55,825
Tell me…

538
00:38:56,705 --> 00:39:00,225
If someone stands on Earth
and keeps walking south,

539
00:39:00,825 --> 00:39:01,825
where do they end up?

540
00:39:03,625 --> 00:39:05,385
Keep going south…

541
00:39:06,585 --> 00:39:07,585
as far south as possible.

542
00:39:12,265 --> 00:39:14,785
You'll reach the South Pole.

543
00:39:15,385 --> 00:39:17,385
But once you're there,

544
00:39:17,465 --> 00:39:20,465
any direction you go
won't be south anymore.

545
00:39:22,225 --> 00:39:25,145
Xiaohe, we're both at the bottom.

546
00:39:26,385 --> 00:39:28,785
Your birthday's March 31.

547
00:39:29,305 --> 00:39:31,185
Mine's June 30.

548
00:39:32,105 --> 00:39:33,785
Last day of the month.

549
00:39:34,385 --> 00:39:35,865
But think of it…

550
00:39:36,625 --> 00:39:40,625
The next day after our birthdays
is always a new month.

551
00:39:42,185 --> 00:39:43,665
I like that.

552
00:39:51,665 --> 00:39:53,065
It's my dad's account.

553
00:39:53,585 --> 00:39:56,345
Uncle Ran wouldn't use his own birthday.

554
00:40:01,185 --> 00:40:03,945
ENTER PASSWORD

555
00:40:07,225 --> 00:40:08,185
GOOD EVENING, HE YUANHANG

556
00:40:09,585 --> 00:40:10,665
Got it!

557
00:40:16,585 --> 00:40:18,585
INBOX: 0 UNREAD

558
00:40:20,025 --> 00:40:21,745
There's nothing.

